{
  "texts": [
    "If |Ψ⟩ has non-zero Chern number, then we could have terms like∼ k F S (k, G) sin ϕ S (k, G) |Ψ⟩.",
    "However TRS T = τ x K, where K is complex conjugation, constrains F S (-k, -q) = F S (k, q) and ϕ S (-k, -q) = ϕ S (k, q).",
    "Using the general property Λ S (k, q) = [Λ S (k + q, -q)] †, we obtain F S (-k, G) = F S (k, G) and ϕ S (-k, G) = -ϕ S (k, G).Therefore the summation over k vanishes, meaning that we have an exact zero-energy ground state.",
    "In fact, the above construction for exact generalized ferromagnetic ground states can be extended to non-zero integer fillings if one imposes an additional 'flat-metric condition' on the form factors [35] 43.",
    "In this way, we have analytic solutions for strong-coupling insulators at every integer ν, which can take various Chern numbers C = 4 -|ν|, 2 -|ν|,..., |ν| -4."
  ]
}